From bb57f3384dc3d19789bdc778359ef5022ccb8636 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Enrique Parodi Spalazzi <enrique.parodi@airbus.com>
Date: Fri, 24 Apr 2026 00:18:03 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 03/10] feat[core/lang]: add query::complete() with positional
 FSM

Tab-completion surface for the query language. complete() walks a
positional FSM (selectKeyword -> classPath -> fromKeyword -> ...)
that tells it what the cursor can produce next, then emits
context-aware candidates:

- Class names prefixed by the registry's qualified names.
- Session and bus names from BusLookup.
- Keywords expected at the current slot (FROM, WHERE, AND, OR, BETWEEN,
  IN, NOT, comparison operators).
- Typed values: when the LHS of a comparison is a known property,
  propose values of the right kind (enum labels for enum props,
  booleans for bool props, quoted strings for string props, ...).

Bundled hygiene refactors that came with complete: drop redundant name
fields from completion variants, centralize token-to-lexeme mapping in
lexemeOf(StlTokenType), and use lexemeOf for keyword completions
instead of hard-coded strings.
